{"search_data": "CentralAajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY) to be Launched Soon \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Objectives of Aajeevika Grameen Express YojanaThe purpose of Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana is to provide an alternative source of livelihoods to members of Self Help Groups (SHGs) under DAY-NRLM. Till now, 34.4 lakh women SHGs have been supported under the programme. The Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana will ensure providing all facilities them to handle public transport services in backward rural areas.AGEY would ensure to provide safe, affordable and community monitored rural transport vehicles to connect each remote villages with main services. The vehicles which will be used under the scheme are\u2013 E-rickshaws \u2013 3 and 4 wheeler motorized transport vehiclesMoreover, AGEY would enable easy connectivity of rural remote areas with all facilities including access to markets, education and health for the overall economic development of the area.Financially Support Under Aajeevika Grameen Express YojanaThe government would provide financiall support under the AGEY in the form of Revolving Fund and Community Investment Funds. This fund would be given as grants to the Self Help Groups (SHGs) and their members/partnership. So far, Central govt. has released a total amount of Rs. 1815 crore to about 3.96 lakh SHGs.Under Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY), One main provision has proposed that the Community Based Organisations (CBO) will provide interest free loan from its own funds to Self Help Group member for purchase of the transport vehicle.This AGEY scheme will have a focus on women empowerment and it has been dedicated to promoting farm and non-farm based livelihoods for women farmers in rural areas.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}